<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN275">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kōṭṭaṅ kaṇṇiyuṅ koṭuntirai yāṭaiyum</l>
<l>vēṭṭatu colli vēntaṉait toṭuttalu</l>
<l>mottaṉṟu mātō vivaṟkē ceṟṟiya</l>
<l>tiṇinilai yalaṟak kūvai pōḻntutaṉ</l>
<l>vaṭimā ṇeḵkaṅ kaṭimukat tēnti</l>
<l>yōmpumi ṉōmpumi ṉivaṇeṉa vōmpātu</l>
<l>toṭarkoḷ yāṉaiyiṟ kuṭarkā ṟaṭpak</l>
<l>kaṉṟamar kaṟavai māṉa</l>
<l>muṉcamat tetirntataṉ ṟōḻaṟku varumē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>A curved chaplet and a dress with curved pleats</l>
<l>and linking up to the king by speaking what is desired</l>
<l>were like him. Crossing </l>
<l>the Kūvai?? so that the resisting firm ranks cry,</l>
<l>holding up to the protective front [his] blade glorious for shape,</l>
<l>not paying attention while they say “beware, beware there!”,</l>
<l>while [his] feet are hindered by intestines like an elephant caught in the fetter</l>
<l>like a cow desirous of [its] calf</l>
<l>he comes towards his friends who earlier one faced [the enemy] in battle.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
